The example in https://github.com/KentBeck/junit/blob/master/src/main/java/org/junit/runners/Parameterized.java appears to have one pair of "{" and "}" too many after "new Object[][]". It doesn't compile.

Here is a fixed version:

	@Parameters
	public static List<Object[]> data() {
		return Arrays.asList(new Object[][] {
			{ 0, 0 }, { 1, 1 }, { 2, 1 }, { 3, 2 }, { 4, 3 }, { 5, 5 }, { 6, 8 }
		});
	}

I am extending ParentRunner<?> with my own implementation using DI and the single constructor check is getting in the way:
<pre>
	public TestClass(Class<?> klass) {
		fClass= klass;
		if (klass != null && klass.getConstructors().length > 1)
			throw new IllegalArgumentException(
					"Test class can only have one constructor");
</pre>
Could this be moved aside to a protected validateXXX method or even move it up to BlockJUnit4ClassRunner?

I am afraid the categories + parameterized duo still does not work properly with fresh junit 4.9 final, yet after #74 changes  the feedback is much better than messageless NPE. Note that the test class has @Category annotation on class level.
