Hi,
A Null Pointer Exception is thrown when using Categories against a set of test classes which include a Test Suite which also includes Tests.  E.g. 

public class MyTestSuite extends TestCase {
           public static Test suite() {
              ...
           }
         
           public void testXYZ() {
               ...
           }
}

A Category need not be specified on the test or test suite. During the Categories.CategoryFilter.shouldRun routine, Categories.CategoryFilter.parentDescription() is called (down the call stack).  The class Descrption, method methodStringMatch() contains a regex expression which doesn't account for the fDisplayName value in this particular case.  fDisplayName ends up with a value that looks like:

TestSuite with 16 tests [example: com.abc.classname]

One fix would be to amend Description.methodStringMatch() to read:

private Matcher methodStringMatcher() {
                Matcher matcher = Pattern.compile("(.*)\\((.*)\\)").matcher(toString());
        	return matcher.matches()
              		? matcher
                	: Pattern.compile("(.* \\[.*: )(.*)\\]").matcher(toString());
}

Please let us know whether this fix can be applied or there is an equivalent fix to or already being applied.

Thanks!

joseph
